Summary of this change
1. Fix test data generation logic (load_data()) 

- Original: The date was hardcoded to 2026-06, causing all statistics for the current month (2026-04) to display 0 
- Now: Change to dynamically fetch the current month and only fill it to today (days_so_far = now.day) 
- Each user changes to an independent power consumption mode (7-day cycle), resulting in differentiated energy saving rates and points results 

2. Added GET /energy-history 

Return all user power consumption records (in reverse order by date) for use by the history.js history page.

3. Added GET /user-data (alias) 

Points to the same energy_history() function called by the index.js chart module. 

4. Added GET /leaderboard-data 

Returns the leaderboard of all users sorted by total_points in descending order, including the ranking field, for use by leaderboard.js. 

5. Added POST /redeem-reward 

Receive username, reward_name, points_required, verify whether the points are enough, deduct them, and save them persistently for use by redeem.js.
